Open github on github.com
login to your account or clone your existing repo to your local or remote machine (on a sandbox in alx evn. for instance)
create your repository and any directories needed.You can do this by using the command cd <repository>, mkdir <directory name>
create file. For example: touch README.md. Use vi to edit the file and use cat <filename> to view file contents
All these can be done in a terminal interface on a local machine, then add, commit and push to github
Any updates must be added,committed, pushed to github. For examples: "git add .", "git push .", "git commit -m 'my commits'"
